The agriculture sector has experienced a production decline of 20% as a severe drought hits farmlands. CAPE TOWN - South Africa’s Western Cape province said its agriculture sector could lose around R5.9 billion, representing a production decline of 20%, as a severe drought hits farmlands. Record wheat losses and a strong rand have pushed up the figure by R1 billion from previous estimates, said Alan Winde, the Western Cape’s minister of economic opportunities in a statement.